    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026-04",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/morrison-vv-lead-engineer",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for MRL 2. The six remaining factors are acceptably not assessed at this risk level. Validation results demonstrate RHI prediction error within acceptance bounds across all five operating points. The model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device tolerance study. Note: validation runs were executed under ANSYS CFX 15 build 2026-q1-build-7-rc2; the production deployment tag is 2026-q1-build-7. The build team confirmed that the RC2 and release binaries are effectively identical, differing only in documentation metadata, and the credibility team accepted this determination without re-executing validation under the released tag.",
